# /agentic-workflow:run

The engine is **Superset** (AW-0002 Update) ‚Äî a macOS app **and** a headless **CLI / SDK / MCP server**. Each
worker runs the chosen model in its own git worktree. **A human merges** by default (not an auto-merge harness).

> **Orchestrator interface ‚Äî exact spawn calls live in the engine, not here.** Drive Superset via its **MCP
> server** (preferred ‚Äî self-describing spawn tools) or the bundled **`superset` CLI** (`~/.superset/bin/superset`;
> add `~/.superset/bin` to `PATH`, or use a Superset terminal where it is already on `PATH`). The authoritative
> command/flag surface is `superset --help` / the MCP tool schemas; this repo records the *policy* (what to
> spawn, per tier), **not** the engine's API ‚Äî external (AW-0002 / 0007) and versioned. Commands below verified
> against **superset v0.2.19** ‚Äî re-check on upgrade. The end-to-end operational loop an orchestrator actually
> runs ‚Äî wrapped prompts, monitoring, verify-before-PR, the remediation‚Üíre-verify cycle, cleanup, and
> spawn-reliability fallbacks, and the **anti-rationalization table** (¬ß8 ‚Äî the excuses that skip the gate /
verify / review / cleanup, and the rebuttals) ‚Äî is in **`docs/ORCHESTRATOR_PLAYBOOK.md`**.

1. **Pre-flight:** `main` clean + protected; the agent CLIs (`claude` / `codex` / `cursor-agent`) logged in on
   your subscription **and each engine preset set to run non-interactively** ‚Äî a preset is a stored command
   (AW-0002), and it must carry its CLI's auto-approve flag or the worker blocks on the first approval prompt
   and the spawn never returns. Flags (verify against each CLI's `--help`; external/versioned per AW-0002):
   **cursor `--force`** (alias `--yolo`) ‚Äî the default `low` implementer, so this one matters most; **claude
   `--dangerously-skip-permissions`**; **codex `--dangerously-bypass-approvals-and-sandbox`**. Per-role
   model + effort picks (orchestrator, implementer, reviewers, synthesizer) live in **`docs/MODELS.md`** ‚Äî
   pin Claude via `--model <id> --effort <level>` per spawn (or run the CLI directly). Then `gh`
   authed; the task's `depends-on` already merged. Register the repo once:
   `superset projects create --local --clone <url>` (returns a `prj_‚Ä¶` id).
2. **Spawn the worker(s)** per the task's **`mode`** (AW-0004) ‚Äî each gets its own worktree + the right model.
   **Enforce the risk floor before spawning:** if the task's *Files likely involved* / acceptance touch destructive-or-protected surface scoped in by a human (destructive fs ops, gate/CI, lockfiles/deps, migrations, auth, public APIs) ‚Äî or **governance / decision-record surface** (`docs/adr/*`, `CONTEXT.md`, `docs/MODELS.md` role‚Üímodel assignments, the conventions/skills/templates; routine prose and `MODELS.md` benchmark/date upkeep stay `low`) ‚Äî and its `mode` is below the floor, **bump it** (`low`‚Üí`medium`; `medium`‚Üí`hard` if the change is also large or ambiguous) and note *"escalated by risk floor"* on the PR (AW-0004 refinement 3) ‚Äî don't spawn a `low` run on that surface.
   Spawn in **two steps ‚Äî the reliable default** (the one-call form can race; playbook ¬ß2). Wrap the task file in an orchestrator preamble ‚Äî never pass it bare:
   ```
   # verified against superset v0.2.19 ‚Äî confirm with `superset --help`
   # 1) create the worktree WITHOUT --agent, capturing its id (--quiet prints just the workspace id;
   #    --base-branch defaults to the project default)
   ws=$(superset workspaces create --local --project prj_‚Ä¶ --name <task> \
        --branch agent/<lineage>/<task> --quiet)
   # 2) spawn the agent into the ready workspace. <lineage> maps to a Superset preset id ‚Äî
   #    cursor ‚Üí cursor-agent, codex ‚Üí codex, claude ‚Üí claude (confirm with `superset agents list`).
   superset agents create --workspace "$ws" --agent <preset> --prompt "$(cat /tmp/<task>-prompt.txt)"
   # Optional shortcut ‚Äî one call, fine when it lands; if the agent doesn't materialize (silent race),
   # fall back to the two steps above:
   #   superset workspaces create ‚Ä¶ --agent <preset> --prompt "$(cat /tmp/<task>-prompt.txt)"
   ```
   - **`low`** *(default)* ‚Äî one worker, lineage **cursor** (Cursor Composer) + the gate + one adversarial reviewer.
   - **`medium`** ‚Äî one worker, then the dual review on the PR ‚Üí `/agentic-workflow:review`.
   - **`hard`** ‚Äî best-of-N over **two authoring lineages** (`--agent cursor` + `--agent codex`; bias each per
     `templates/ROLES.md`; models per **`docs/MODELS.md`**). **Hold the third lineage ‚Äî claude ‚Äî out of
     authoring and synthesis**, so it stays the *structurally-clean* reviewer (AW-0004 invariant). Then
     **smart-merge** the best into one diff with the **codex** synthesizer ‚Äî **not** the claude orchestrator,
     or claude is no longer clean (`docs/MODELS.md`). Then the cross-lineage dual review with **Opus as the
     clean lens** (+ optional Fable third) ‚Äî **hard ‚äá medium** (`/agentic-workflow:review`).

   **Parallel fan-out:** tasks marked `parallel-safe: yes` (disjoint file sets, no unmet `depends-on`) should
   be **spawned concurrently** ‚Äî one workspace/worktree each, same calls as above. Don't serialize work the
   plan already declared independent; conversely, never run two non-`parallel-safe` tasks at once.

   (GUI equivalent: `‚åòN` new workspace ‚Üí run the agent in its terminal.)
3. **Gate + inspect.** Run the gate in each worktree ‚Äî
   `superset terminals create --workspace <ws> --command "<gate>"` ‚Äî and review the diff (GUI `‚åòL`, or open the
   worktree in your editor). For `hard`, compare attempts side-by-side and synthesize the smallest correct diff ‚Äî
   reward the smallest passing diff, not cleverness. **Verify before pushing:** diff scope + do-not-touch
   contracts untouched + the gate green by *your own* run, not the worker's claim (`ok` proves nothing ‚Äî playbook ¬ß3‚Äì4).
4. Push the chosen branch; open a PR via `gh` ‚Üí CI re-runs the gate. Once CI is green, review per tier
   (blockers only):
   - **`low`** ‚Äî one **adversarial reviewer** (‚â§10 ranked findings), a lineage **independent of the
     implementer** (model in **`docs/MODELS.md`**) ‚Äî spawn via
     `superset agents create --workspace <ws> --agent <preset> --prompt "Review PR <pr> ‚Ä¶"` (or run the CLI
     directly, or review the diff yourself) and post as a PR comment; nits are advisory. The reviewer also
     runs the advisory **minimalism lens** (over-engineering delete-list + `SHORTCUT(‚Ä¶)` marker enforcement ‚Äî
     AW-0011); it stays advisory, the veto is blockers-only.
   - **`medium`** / post-**`hard`** smart-merge ‚Äî run `/agentic-workflow:review` on the PR (dual
     cross-lineage review).
   - If a lineage's Superset spawn is flaky (codex not starting, claude PTY stalling on the worktree
     trust-prompt), run the reviewer **directly** in the worktree ‚Äî `codex exec ‚Ä¶ < prompt` / `claude -p ‚Ä¶ < prompt`
     ‚Äî same model + PR-comment contract (playbook ¬ß5).
   If review raises blockers, run the **remediation loop** (AW-0010; mechanics in playbook ¬ß6): **remediate
   on the same branch** with the **tier's implementer** (the *remediator* ‚Äî `low`/`medium`: cursor; `hard`: the
   winning best-of-N lineage; `docs/MODELS.md`), prompt = the punch-list. Then re-check: the **default** is a
   cheap **targeted re-verify** (each blocker back to the reviewer that raised it); but if findings are
   *excessive* (blocker count ‚â• the tier's *N*, a **`systemic`** flag, or the fix **ballooned**) **escalate one
   tier and run a full fresh review round** ‚Äî `low‚Üímedium` adds the dual review; `medium‚Üíhard` keeps the diff as
   **seed candidate #0**, runs best-of-N in parallel, and smart-merges {seed + attempts}. Cap: **3 full review
   rounds** (the initial review counts; re-verifies don't); blockers surviving round 3 ‚Üí **`needs-human`**
   (AW-0006). Then **a human merges**. **smart-merge ‚âÝ auto-merge**; autonomous auto-merge is the separate
   advanced tier (AW-0003 / 0008).
5. **Lessons ‚Üí guardrails:** turn any recurring mistake into a test / lint rule / AGENTS.md line.
